{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17491164","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17491164"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T05:35:49+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T05:35:49+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"852"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"852","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/852"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.25,0.05,0.13,0.17,0.4]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"852"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"108802"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"852","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/852"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"852"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"91165"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"30"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"552"},{"type":"tags","id":"934"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"5697"},{"type":"contributions","id":"6680"},{"type":"contributions","id":"38273"},{"type":"contributions","id":"38480"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"108802","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/108802"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe plain radiograph is useful for defining foreign objects in the abdominal cavity - whether they were placed there intentionally or otherwise. This patient had undergone a surgical procedure. As part of the procedure a device is inserted and is clearly visible on the plain abdominal radiograph (Image). It is often possible to determine the type of procedure that was performed just by looking at the \u0027foreign body\u0027 and by knowing what that is used for.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following was the condition that was being treated in this case?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Persistent ascites","Extending iliac vein thrombosis","Benign intracranial hypertension","Abdominal aortic aneurysm","Obesity"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe X-ray shows an adjustable gastric band, used in the treatment of \u003Cstrong\u003Eobesity\u003C/strong\u003E. The two rings seen near the middle of the X-ray are part of the subcutaneous port, used to access and either inflate or deflate the band.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EA peritoneovenous shunt (LeVeen or Denver shunt), is a device used to shunt ascites to the superior vena cava (SVC) in patients with \u003Cstrong\u003Epersistent ascites. \u003C/strong\u003EThe proximal end is placed within the peritoneal cavity and the shunt is tunnelled in the subcutaneous tissues over the anterior chest wall and into the internal jugular vein.\u00a0It is best seen in on a chest X-ray, where the shunt can be found tracking from below the diaphragm to the SVC by way of the internal jugular vein.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EExtending iliac vein thrombosis \u003C/strong\u003Eby itself\u003Cstrong\u003E \u003C/strong\u003Ewould not be visible on an abdominal X-ray and requires alternative imaging modalities such as doppler ultrasound or CT venography. This problem is often treated by insertion of an inferior vena cava filter. The aim of the filter is to lessen the risk of pulmonary embolus complication. On an abdominal X-ray the filter would be visible on the right adjacent to the vertebral bodies within the IVC.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EVentriculoperitoneal (VP) shunts are devices used to shunt cerebrospinal fluid\u00a0(CSF) in the treatment of \u003Cstrong\u003Ebenign intracranial hypertension \u003C/strong\u003Eand hydrocephalus. As suggested by the name, a catheter is placed proximally in the ventricle with the distal catheter tunnelled under the skin and into the peritoneal cavity. The external portion of the catheter is connected to a valve that regulates the flow of CSF based on a preset pressure. A \u0027VP shunt\u0027 series can be done to assess the placement, tracking from the skull down to the abdomen. On abdominal X-ray, the shunt can be seen tracking within the abdomen.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAbdominal aortic aneurysm \u003C/strong\u003Ecan be repaired either via endovascular or \u0027open\u0027 approach. On abdominal X-ray, evidence of fixation by use of a stent or graft may be seen to reflect the outline of the abdominal aorta and iliac arteries.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Adjustable gastric bands can be used in the management of obesity and may be seen centrally on abdominal xray"],"references":["Sonavane SK, Menias CO, Kantawala KP, Shanbhogue AK, Prasad SR, Eagon JC, et al. Laparoscopic adjustable gastric banding: what radiologists need to know. Radiographics. 2012;32(4):1161-78. Available at: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/22787000/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"91165"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"852"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"16251"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"media","id":"16251","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/16251"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/071ab07e-f511-4aeb-ac92-a9beeca0b33a.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/071ab07e-f511-4aeb-ac92-a9beeca0b33a.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":361,"height":440}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"91165","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/91165"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-07-13T14:51:07+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-07-13T14:51:46+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8